Field Documentation

UINT32 CodecDevice::AudioCodecCapabilities::m_application_categories
 

All the supported application categories flag bits will be set (see CodecDevice::ApplicationCategoriesFlagsType), e.g. if the codec supports both Storage & Streaming then it will be set to "3".

CodecType* CodecDevice::AudioCodecCapabilities::m_array_of_supported_codecs
 

Array of the supported audio codecs. The number of elements is given by m_num_of_supported_codecs.

UINT16 CodecDevice::AudioCodecCapabilities::m_max_quality_level
 

Maximum supported quality level.

UINT16 CodecDevice::AudioCodecCapabilities::m_min_quality_level
 

Minimum supported quality level. 0 corresponds to default settings.

UINT8 CodecDevice::AudioCodecCapabilities::m_num_of_supported_codecs
 

Number of supported audio codecs. It is also the length (number of elements) of m_array_of_supported_codecs.
